title: Autism Journey Ride & Century
description: This is a charity ride benefiting Central Georgia Autism. The ride will start at Sandy Beach Park in Macon Georgia. There will be three routes to choose from, 33, 66 and 100 mile options. This will be a full supported ride with rest stops, SAG and bike repair. This event is also sanctioned and insured by USA Cycling.
course: 33, 66 and 100 mile options. Routes will be posted on ride website www.maconcenturyride.com and the ride flyer.
registration: Registration will be handled online through USA Cycling. On-site registration will be available on the day of the event.  One-day USA Cycling license is available for $5, and provides you with medical insurance coverage if involved in an accident during the ride.  Riders who pre-register are guaranteed to get an event t-shirt with their registration.
notes: All riders must sign the USA Cycling waiver before being allowed to participate in the event.  Registering online will allow you to sign the waiver electronically, and speed up your experience at packet pick-up.

title: Off-Road Warrior Time Trials
description:
You asked for it. And you got it!

Time Trials will be at East Athens Community Park, less than 2 miles from the downtown race course.  The time trial will start at 9am. Racers will be assigned start times. Top 50 times across all categories will qualify into the nighttime Off-Road Warrior Criterium.

The Off-Road Warrior Criterium will held on the tradition 4-corner Twilight course and will be 30 minutes long.  Payout will be $500/10 deep.
course: Time Trial course is 1.8 miles and located in East Athens Community Park, just miles from downtown Athens, GA
registration:
register online: https://www.bikereg.com/Net/18674

registration closes on Thursday, April 25 @ 10AM. Day-of registration will be accepted with a $10 late fee. 

$4 from entry fee donated directly to Habitat for Humanity.
notes: Top 50 overall times will move on to the Off-Road Warrior Criterium. Payout for the criterium is $500/10 deep
directions:
From Downtown Athens:
Head North on College Ave. Turn right onto E. Dougherty Street. Turn left onto North Ave. Turn right onto Strickland ave. Continue onto First Street. Turn left onto Trail Creek Street.

title: Dingo CX & Dingo Swap p/b Hayes Chevrolet Chrysler Dodge Jeep RAM
description:
2-day Cyclocross Race and Swap Meet p/b Hayes Chevrolet Chrysler Dodge Jeep RAM of Baldwin and located on the property.

Swap meet attendance is free for shoppers and offers front row view to Dingo Cross Action.
course: Sat course same location, but different layout than Sun.
registration: Planning to participate in Swap Meet, for booth reservation and pricing, contact: betty@feedyourdingo.com
notes:
The Fine Print:
•	All non-licensed racers must purchase either a one-day USAC license for $10 or an annual license for $60 ($30 for juniors), and compete in the applicable CX5, Junior, Women CX4 or SS race.
•	If a racer wishes to enter a second “Adult” race during the day, the entry fee is $10. The entry fee for the first race is the amount of the more expensive race if applicable.
•	Registration closes 15 minutes before the start of each race.  
•	Warm up will be permitted on the course only between events at the official’s discretion and only after waiver has been signed. 
•	Race is held rain or shine. 
•	Helmets must be worn at all times while riding bike. 
•	Mountain bikes are permitted but bar ends must be removed. 
•	The promoter reserves the right to combine categories and/or prizes due to attendance. Categories under 5 racers may be combined.
directions:
From the Atlanta: Take I-85 North, Continue on I-985 N/Following signs for Gainesville, I-985 becomes GA-365. The Hayes Dealership is on the Right, just North of Wilbanks Rd. 
Address: 3656 Hwy 365, Alto, GA (or Baldwin, GA)
